(1, '<h2>Your About Us page is vital.</h2>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s often the first step in any user&rsquo;s journey through a website or blog.</p>\r\n<p>It also shouldn&rsquo;t be their last, because first impressions count online just as much as they do in the real world.</p>\r\n<p>If your visitors aren&rsquo;t impressed, you can expect them to leave without reading your awesome content or completing a conversion action (e.g., signing up for your newsletter, making a purchase).</p>\r\n<p>What Makes a Solid &lsquo;About Us&rsquo; Page?</p>\r\n<p>Your About Us page should be:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Informative. It doesn&rsquo;t always have to tell the whole story, but it should at least provide people with an idea of who and what you are.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Contain social proof, testimonials, and some personal information that viewers can relate to such as education, family, etc.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Useful and engaging.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Easy to navigate and accessible on any device.</strong></p>\r\n<p>That may all sound complicated, but it really isn&rsquo;t.</p>\r\n<p>The main purpose of your About Us page is to give visitors a glimpse into the identity of either a person or business.</p>\r\n<p>As users discover your brand, they need to distinguish what sets you apart and makes you&hellip; you.</p>\r\n<p>This often requires finding the right balance between compelling content and a design carefully planned to look the part.</p>\r\n<p>Conveying your identity in a fun and approachable &ndash; but also reliable and informative &ndash; way is challenging.</p>\r\n<p>If you know who you are and your goal for your site, the About Us page should come naturally.</p>\r\n<p>However, if you&rsquo;re looking for some inspiration, you can always check out these 25 examples of creative and engaging About Us pages.</p>\r\n<p>These excellent examples will help you build a personal and engaging website journey.</p>', '2019-08-06 18:38:04', '2019-08-06 12:38:04');

